org.apache.juneau.uon

Class UonParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.juneau.CoreObject
      • org.apache.juneau.parser.Parser
        • org.apache.juneau.parser.ReaderParser
          • org.apache.juneau.uon.UonParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    UonParser.Decoding, UrlEncodingParser

    @Consumes(value="text/uon")
public class UonParser
extends ReaderParser
    Parses UON (a notation for URL-encoded query parameter values) text into POJO models.
    Media types:

    Handles Content-Type types: text/uon

    Description:

    This parser uses a state machine, which makes it very fast and efficient.

    Configurable properties:

    This class has the following properties associated with it:

    • UonParserContext
    • ParserContext
    • BeanContext

        public UonParserSession createSession(Object input,
                                      ObjectMap op,
                                      Method javaMethod,
                                      Object outer,
                                      Locale locale,
                                      TimeZone timeZone,
                                      MediaType mediaType)
        Description copied from class: Parser
        Create the session object that will be passed in to the parse method.

        It's up to implementers to decide what the session object looks like, although typically it's going to be a subclass of ParserSession.

        Overrides:
        createSession in class Parser
        Parameters:
        input - The input. See Parser.parse(Object, ClassMeta) for supported input types.
        op - Optional additional properties.
        javaMethod - Java method that invoked this parser. When using the REST API, this is the Java method invoked by the REST call. Can be used to access annotations defined on the method or class.
        outer - The outer object for instantiating top-level non-static inner classes.
        locale - The session locale. If null, then the locale defined on the context is used.
        timeZone - The session timezone. If null, then the timezone defined on the context is used.
        mediaType - The session media type (e.g. "application/json").
        Returns:
        The new session.
